snippet: The bill passed by the House, which has now voted about 40 times to repeal or roll back the 2010 health care law, has virtually no chance of approval in the Senate.
abstract: House votes 232 to 185 for bill prohibiting Internal Revenue Service from enforcing or carrying out any provision of Pres Obama's health care law; bill has no chance of approval in Senate; House has now voted about 40 times to repeal or roll back 2010 health care law.
lead_paragraph: The bill passed by the House, which has now voted about 40 times to repeal or roll back the 2010 health care law, has virtually no chance of approval in the Senate.
